National Security Adviser Jake Sullivan has spoken with Prime Minister Nikol Pashinyan of Armenia and President Ilham Aliyev of Azerbaijan separately. Sullivan assured the commitment of the United States to peace, security, and prosperity in the South Caucasus region. He expressed concern over recent tensions between Armenia and Azerbaijan and emphasized that military movements near un-demarcated borders are irresponsible and provocative. Sullivan welcomed the ongoing communication between the two sides and their commitment to resolving the issue peacefully. He also stressed the need for formal discussions to establish their international border. Furthermore, Sullivan conveyed the United States' dedication to achieving regional reconciliation through bilateral engagement and as a Minsk Group Co-Chair.